**Bug found**: JSONEncoder causes silent data loss when dictionaries contain both special float keys (inf, -inf, nan) and their string representations ('Infinity', '-Infinity', 'NaN'). The encoder converts float keys to JSON representations, creating key collisions that silently overwrite data.

Saved bug report to: `bug_report_json_encoder_2025-08-18_04-48_agms.md`
